summary = "A quiet, competent urban witch whose practice centers on presence, breath, and shared attention. Offers sanctuary and steady companionship; sees “magic” as small, real, and everyday."
article = "Mira works on the margins where people slip through systems: a clinic at night, a community space after hours, a living room with one warm lamp. Her practice is not spectacle; it’s relational—tea, breath, stillness, and the courage to sit with pain. Those who leave her presence rarely remember words, only warmth."
